# Project Rules

## Typography
- Always use Sora font for headings (H1, H2, H3) via `font-sora` class or CSS variable `--font-sora`
- Always use Inter font for body text, subtitles, and captions via `font-inter` class or CSS variable `--font-inter`
- Never use Sora for body text
- Never use Inter for headings

## Design System
- Never use emojis in any file (code, text, comments)
- Never use gradients; only solid colors from the specified design system
- Use only these colors from the palette:
  - `deep-space-blue`: `#090909`
  - `atomic-tangerine`: `#ff6b35`
  - `amber-honey`: `#eca406`
  - `cetacean-blue`: `#01091C`
  - `oxford-blue`: `#061A4B`
  - `anti-flash-white`: `#F2F2F2`

## Project Structure
- Keep the project as a single Next.js app in the root (no monorepo layout)
- Do not create `apps/` folder or similar
- The `app/` directory lives inside `src/` (src/app/)
- All project files must live in the repo root (standard Next.js structure)

## Styling
- Prefer consistent components and styling aligned with this design system
- Use Tailwind utility classes
- Container max-width should be between 960px-1200px (e.g., `max-w-5xl` or `max-w-6xl`)
- Maintain vertical spacing between blocks: 40-64px
- Maintain vertical padding inside blocks: 32-48px
